messages.message:
I see a really weird problem happening on instabase.com (http://instabase.com) with the military_02 US markets flow: the `"text"` field of the IBOCR file doesn’t match up with what `review-doc` shows us (refer to attached images) on the s3_apply_refiner step’s output.

The `"text"` field was correct for both prior two steps. Anyone know what could be up?

Example file: https://www.instabase.com/apps/ocr/review-batch/ib_solutions/solutions/fs/Instabase%20Drive/pre-built/us-markets/paystubs/samples/Military_02_paystub/run_chetan/2019-10-15-23:16:50/73aa8197-569a-4f4c-88bb-21ab2642f9a6/out/s3_apply_refiner/paystub_1503434326137.PDF.ibocr
Logging out for the day but will look at replies tomorrow
@Kerry @Aaron Tami @shaunak — was this some issues we used to see back in the day with the criss-cross bug?
